Sentencas: Double-perovskite materials La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+delta (LPBCO), suitable for the application of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC) and other electrochemical devices, were successfully prepared through solid-state reaction method.
Titulo: A-site double-lanthanide-doped La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of La and Pr doping ratios on the crystallographic structure, thermochemical stability, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity, and electrochemical polarizations were analyzed and discussed.
Titulo: A-site double-lanthanide-doped La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction results show that the crystal structure changes from single perovskite to double perovskite with the increase in Pr doping content.
Titulo: A-site double-lanthanide-doped La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LPBCOs present excellent chemical stability with conventional electrolyte GDC at less than 1100 degrees C.
Titulo: A-site double-lanthanide-doped La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion can be effectively reduced upon doping of Pr.
Titulo: A-site double-lanthanide-doped La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The materials demonstrate high electrical conductivity even under relatively low temperatures, i.e., LP-73 (x = 0.3 with single perovskite) has the highest conductivity at 1680 S/cm at 400 degrees C. Among the double-perovskite compositions, LP-55 presents the highest performance in electrical conductivity though.
Titulo: A-site double-lanthanide-doped La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Analysis of the electrochemical impedance spectra of LPBCOs symmetric cells reveals low area specific polarization resistances for these double-lanthanide-doped double-perovskite materials, and the charge transfer is determined as the dominating sub-process for the oxygen transport through the materials.
Titulo: A-site double-lanthanide-doped La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All the findings show that La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+delta possesses excellent oxygen reduction activity and is promising for the application in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: A-site double-lanthanide-doped La1-xPrxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
